    "The Indian Leader DEVOTED TO INDIAN EDUCATIOI VOL IX HASKELL INSTITUTE LAWRENCE KANSAS NOVEMBER 17 1905 NO 28 ROOM ATTHETOP Never you mind the crowd lad Or fancy your life wont tell The work is the work for a that To him that doeth it well Fancy the world a hill lad Look where the millions stop Youll find the crowd at the base lad Theres always room at the top Courage and faith and patience Theres space in the old world yet The bet er the chance you stand lad The further along you get Keep your eye on the goal lad Never despair or drop Be sure your path leads upwards Theres always room at the top A BRIEF ACCOUNT OFTHE MOHONK CONFERENCE 11 B PE AIKS As is the usual custom those who were fortunate enough to have been in vited to attend the Lake Mohonk Con ference were met at New Paltz by con veyances from the Mountain Summer Hotel and were taken over the beauti ful drives across the valley and over the mountains down to the wonderful little lake upon which is situated the Lake Mohonk House New Paltz is sit uated about six"
